UNOFFICIAL COPY 25 RS BR 1929
1 AN ACT relating to small farms and home-based processors.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS 217.015 TO 217.215 IS CREATED
4 TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section, "small farm" means land:
6 (a) That is used for growing crops or raising livestock;
7 (b) From which a person prepares or sells food products; and
8 (c) From which not more than one million five hundred thousand dollars
9 ($1,500,000) in gross sales, in a single year, is received from:
10 1. Livestock products;
11 2. Cultivated or harvested crops; or
12 3. The sale of food products.
13 (2) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the state, and any city,
14 county, urban-county governments, consolidated local government, unified local
15 government, or charter county government and any health department thereof
16 shall not impose any rule, administrative regulation, certification, or licensing
17 requirement that is not required under federal law on a:
18 (a) Small farm; or
19 (b) Home-based processor.
20 Section 2. The following KRS section is repealed:
21 217.136 Home-based food processors -- Exemption from permit requirement and fair
22 packaging and labeling laws -- Production, labeling, and sales of home-processed
23 food products -- Inspections -- Registration system.
